@B: Yes, it's easy to get frustrated when we don't see progress right away, but it's important to trust the process and keep going.
@C: I think it's also important to find a learning method that works best for you, whether it's through classes, online tutorials, or hands-on practice.
@D: I completely agree. Hands-on practice and feedback from others can be incredibly valuable in learning a new skill.

Drucker: Learning a new skill can be a daunting task, but it's important to remember that it's an investment in yourself. By being patient, persistent, and finding a learning method that works best for you, you can build up your knowledge and skills to achieve your goals.

